questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directions:&lt;/strong&gt; Study the following graph carefully to answer the given question:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;% of students as per Department wise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Find the number of students in Mech and Civil dept.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/12/State%20Govt._Akash_Akansha_13.12.2022_G1.PNG&quot; style=&quot; width: 310px; height: 345px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The percentage of students as per department wise is given&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculations:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total number of students = 12200&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The percentage of students in the mechanical department is 19%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of students in mechanical department = 19% of 12200&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;12200 &amp;times; &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\dfrac{19}{100}\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;=&amp;nbsp;2318&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percentage of students in Civil department = 20%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Number of students in Civil department = 20% of 12200&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;12200 &amp;times; &lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\dfrac{20}{100}\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;= 2440&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total students in mechanical and Civil department = (2318 + 2440) = 4758&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The answer is 4758&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;The following chart shows the expenditure of a house on various heads. The total expenditure of the house is Rs. 85,200. Study the chart and answer the question.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/25/07/chart%20%2816%29.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 452px; height: 280px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How much more amount is spent on ration than on rent?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Money spends on ration is 36%.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Money spends on Rent&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt; is 20%.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Difference = 36% - 20% = 16%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;According to the question.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;16% of 85,200 = Rs. 13,632&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; Option 3 is the correct answer.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
